{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"cinnamoned-tzarist-kangaroo","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nCapture env/integration-diagnosis passively by adding an additive `verdict=\"ERROR\"` outcome with an `error{cause,evidence_ref}` object on the gates' infrastructure-exception path, so a diagnosis interval starts (ERROR) and ends (next PASS) is recorded by gate code, never by agent self-report.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py` — classify an infra exception (provider 5xx/connection/tooling) vs a domain BLOCK/FAIL; on infra, write an ERROR sidecar before re-raising.\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py`, `src/rebar/llm/completion_sidecar.py` — add an optional `ERROR` verdict + `error` object to the payload builders (default-absent).\n- `tests/unit/workflow/test_gate_error_sidecar.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nThe `REVIEW_RESULT`/`COMPLETION_VERDICT` sidecars are non-replay events that survive compaction and already carry a `metrics` block — the natural home, so no new event type is introduced. The ERROR outcome is additive/optional (default preserves old-record semantics; older readers see no ERROR rows), keeping it back-compatible; back-out = stop writing ERROR. Only gate-encountered infra failures are captured — a deliberate, stated scope limit (shell/CI toil outside a gate stays out of scope). Stamped by gate code on a real failure, so the self-report reliability problem does not apply.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit: a stubbed gate run raising a connection error writes a sidecar with `verdict=ERROR` and non-empty `error.cause`, then re-raises; a domain BLOCK writes no ERROR.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/workflow/test_gate_error_sidecar.py` passes: injecting an infra exception yields a persisted sidecar with `jq -e '.verdict==\"ERROR\"'` and non-empty `error.cause`, and the exception still propagates.\n- [ ] a domain BLOCK/FAIL produces no ERROR sidecar — unit test asserts absence.","id":"8bc5-9c76-95f3-465e","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","schema"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Gate ERROR outcome on the infra-exception path (env-diagnosis start)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416828704053001,"uuid":"cbdafdc2-1959-40b3-9a45-76eb5d8f3f8f"}